Pammene spiniana is a moth belonging to the family Tortricidae. The species was first described by Philog√®ne Auguste Joseph Duponchel in 1842.It is native to Europe.
The wingspan is 10-11 mm. The forewings are dark fuscous,with obscure violet - metallic striae, and the costa obscurely paler strigulated.There is a triangular white median dorsal spot, usually
enclosing an obscure fuscous dorsal dot. The hindwings are fuscous, in the male with a broad terminal and dorsal dark fuscous fascia, in the female darker throughout.